cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Phorj in your research or work, please cite it as below."
title: "Phorj"
abstract: >-
  A small, statically-typed, PHP-inspired programming language implemented in Rust (std-only,
  zero external crates). Runs on two byte-identical backends — a tree-walking interpreter and a
  bytecode stack VM — transpiles to PHP, and compiles to standalone native executables.
type: software
authors:
